Title : Democratic Party for Justice
Text : {{Politics of Mali}}

The '''Democratic Party for Justice''' ({{lang-fr|Parti DÃ©mocratique pour la Justice}}, PDJ) is a political party in [[Mali]] led by [[Abdoul Ba]].

==History==
The party was established in 1991 and officially registered on 19 April 1991.<ref>[http://www.izf.net/sites/default/files/EE_Partis%20Politiques_19_09_2012.pdf Directory of Political Parties] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502214724/http://www.izf.net/sites/default/files/EE_Partis%20Politiques_19_09_2012.pdf |date=2014-05-02 }} Ministry of the Interior</ref> It received 2.4% of the vote in the [[Malian parliamentary election, July 1997|July 1997 parliamentary elections]], winning a single seat.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/ml.html Elections in Mali] African Elections Database</ref> It joined the [[Alliance for the Republic and Democracy]] prior to the [[Malian parliamentary election, 2002|2002 parliamentary elections]]. The Alliance won 59 seats in total, with the PDJ winning one.<ref>[http://www.panapress.com/Espoir-2002-Alliance-finishes-atop-parliamentary-polls-in-Mali--13-462757-18-lang2-index.html Espoir 2002 Alliance finishes atop parliamentary polls in Mali] Panapress, 10 August 2002</ref>

The party did not contest the [[Malian parliamentary election, 2013|2013 parliamentary elections]].<ref>[http://www.matcl.gov.ml/PDF/SITUAT_PARTICI_PP_LEGISL2013.pdf Participation status of political parties in the 2013 legislative elections]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Ministry of the Interior</ref>

